1
00:00:01,042 --> 00:00:03,336
星际之门之亚特兰蒂斯 前情提要
<i>Previously on Stargate Atlantis</i>

2
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:05,213
它正冲城市飞去!
It's headed for the city !

3
00:00:05,505 --> 00:00:07,673
- 它在干什么?
- 扫描我们 ..
- What's it doing ?
- Scanning us ..

4
00:00:09,091 --> 00:00:11,469
那艘飞船已经向宇宙深处
传送了一些信号
Now the dart sent a transmission deep into space,

5
00:00:11,511 --> 00:00:13,387
然后在我们可以靠近的时候自毁了
and then it self destructed before we could get to it.

6
00:00:13,429 --> 00:00:16,349
- 已经用我们的深空探测器扫描了那片区域..
- 那些是什么?
- We scanned the area with our deep-space sensors and..
- What are those ?

7
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:18,434
幽灵的母船 一共有三艘
Wraith hives ship. Three of them.

8
00:00:18,476 --> 00:00:19,268
它们飞向哪里?
Where are they headed ?

9
00:00:19,310 --> 00:00:22,688
如果保持现在的方向和速度
三周后它们将会到达我们的星球
If they maintain direction and speed,
they'll be over our planet within two weeks.

10
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:33,366
我们已经知道他们要来了
至少现在知道了它们何时会来
We knew they were comming,
at least now we know when.

11
00:00:33,449 --> 00:00:35,284
- 一定有办法
- 有办法?
- That's something.
- That's something ?

12
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:38,579
我们还有时间, Rodney.
现在没有理由恐慌
There's still time, Rodney.
There's no reason to panic...

13
00:00:39,830 --> 00:00:41,916
只要还有时间, 就一定会有希望
- yet.
- Where there is time, there is hope.

14
00:00:42,291 --> 00:00:43,835
同意 有什么建议?
Agreed. So recommandations ?

15
00:00:44,001 --> 00:00:47,046
- 除了恐慌之外?
- 除了恐慌, 是的!
- Other than panic ?
- Other than panic, yes!

16
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:52,051
我知道这可能不是很好
不过我们可以考虑 M7G-677...
I realize this might not be cool,
but we should consider M7G-677.

17
00:00:52,426 --> 00:00:54,804
- 作为一个可能的疏散点?
- 不, 女士
- As a possible evacuation site ?
- No ma'am.

18
00:00:55,054 --> 00:00:57,515
我建议我们取走他们的ZPM
I'm suggesting we take their ZPM.

19
00:00:57,932 --> 00:00:59,642
他们唯一防护幽灵的途径?
Their only means of protection from the Wraith ?

20
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:02,895
一个大部分由孩子居住的星球
A planet populated mostly by children.

21
00:01:03,312 --> 00:01:09,151
他的观点是有根据的
我们已经确定了那个ZPM已经快枯竭了
不过对我们可能还有些用
He raises a valid point. We've already
established the ZPM is nearly depleted,
but it could be of some limited use to us.

22
00:01:09,318 --> 00:01:12,113
你刚才让我们提建议
这是我们生存下来的一种方法
You asked for suggestions. It's a matter of survival.

23
00:01:12,488 --> 00:01:13,573
我知道了
I see.

24
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:19,078
我们还没有走到那一步
只要我还在掌管这里, 我们永远也不会去那里
We're not quite there yet.
And as long as I'm in charge, we will never be there.

25
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,580
我同意Weir博士的观点
I agree doctor Weir.

26
00:01:20,621 --> 00:01:24,625
即便这就是我们的结局
我们也应该体面的应对它
If this is to be our end, it is best
we face it with both dignity and honor.

27
00:01:24,709 --> 00:01:28,129
- 实际上我有一个想法, 除了恐慌之外
- 说出来听听
- To that end I actually have an idea, in addition, to panic.
- Let's hear it.

28
00:01:28,379 --> 00:01:33,467
虽然比较繁琐, 不过我想还是值得的
当然, 大部分要归功于我的...
It's really a long shot, but I think it's most likely
worth the effort, of course the most to be my efforts...

29
00:01:33,509 --> 00:01:34,719
到底是什么?
What is it ?

30
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:38,389
我想我们可以通过星际之门
给地球发回一条消息
I think we can send a message
back to Earth through the Stargate.

31
00:01:38,514 --> 00:01:40,808
- 抱歉?
- 我想我们没有足够的能量
- Excuse me ?
- I thought we didn't have enough power.

32
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:44,353
对于传送一个人来说, 确实不够
我们没有办法让虫洞维持足够长的时间
Not to send a person, no. We'd never be
able to maintain the wormhole long enough.

33
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:47,690
不过我想如果我们把所有可以用的
能源集中到一起
But I think if we would be able to tie together
all of our power generating capabilities,

34
00:01:47,773 --> 00:01:52,486
我们可能, 我强调的一下, 是可能
建立一个足够久的虫洞并发送一条消息
we might - and I emphasise might - be able to establish
a wormhole long enough to send a message.

35
00:01:52,486 --> 00:01:54,030
大概是多长时间?
How much time are we talking about ?

36
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:57,408
大约, 1.3 秒, 发送或者接收
Aproximatly, 1.3 seconds, give or take.

37
00:01:57,617 --> 00:02:00,828
- 这时间不够
- 只够喊SOS了
- That's not much time.
- Time enough to say S.O.S.

38
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:06,709
不是用模拟方式
如果需要发送的消息是经过了高度压缩的
1.3秒完全足够了
Don't be so analogue. 1.3 seconds is
more than enough time to send the message
if it's in the form of a high compression data burst.

39
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:09,670
几年前, 我曾经帮助美国空军
优化过编码算法
Now, I helped refine the encoding
for the US Air Force a few years back.

40
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:14,217
- Carter上校在那边应该知道如何解密
- 你建议我们现在就开始干?
- Colonel Carter should be able to decipher it on the other side.
- You're suggesting this now ?

41
00:02:14,258 --> 00:02:18,638
因为它可能不会成功, 而且很有可能
在进行当中会让我们的发电机过载
Because it probably won't work, and there's
a very good chance it could overload
our naquadah generators in the process.

42
00:02:18,738 --> 00:02:20,640
好啊, 那我们就不应该去冒这个险!
Well then we can't take the risk !

43
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:23,434
没有能量, 我们就没有任何机会了
No power, we won't have a chance in hell.

44
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:28,814
有三艘幽灵的母船正朝这里飞来, 少校
非常时候就应该采取非常措施
There are three Wraith hives ship on the way, Major.
Desperate times call for desperate measures.

45
00:02:29,106 --> 00:02:32,109
除此之外, 我过去几天一直在想办法
尽量让失败的可能性降到最低
Besides, I spent the last few days
working of ways of minimizing the risk.

46
00:02:33,486 --> 00:02:37,615
假如这是可能的, 我们可以发送多少信息?
Assuming it's possible, how much information can we send ?

47
00:02:37,823 --> 00:02:43,955
任何东西 亚特兰蒂斯所有资深组员的
任务报告, 所有我们在飞马座学到的东西
Everything. I mean, mission reports from all
the senior staff, a ton of stuff on Atlantis,
things we've learned in Pegasus.

48
00:02:44,288 --> 00:02:47,166
- 所有的? 一秒钟?
- 一点三秒
- All that ? One second ?
- One point three.

49
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:51,754
我还可以更加优化压缩比率
你们会找着东西来加进去的
You jest, but if I could finesse the compression
ratios, you'll be looking for things to add.

50
00:02:56,717 --> 00:02:59,011
- 做吧
- 就开始
- Do it.
- Doing it.

51
00:03:14,026 --> 00:03:18,322
Elizabeth, 你应该知道
如果星际之门的指挥官能够发出求救信号...
Elizabeth, you realize that if
Stargate Command was able to send help..

52
00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:23,286
我知道 不过我们仍然有责任报告
我们在这里学习到的东西
I know. They would have. But still we've the
responsability to report what we've learned here.

53
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:26,289
- 关于亚特兰蒂斯, 关于古人...
- 幽灵?
- About Atlantis, about the Ancients..
- The Wraith ?

54
00:03:26,455 --> 00:03:28,791
是的, 我们必须提醒地球
Exactly. We have to warn Earth.

55
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,793
即使这是我们所做的最后一件事?
Even if it's the last thing we do ?

56
00:03:30,918 --> 00:03:33,087
如果是最后一件事, 那就尤其如此
Especially if it's the last thing we do.

57
00:04:26,884 --> 00:04:33,013
星际之门之亚特兰蒂斯
第一季第17集 飞马座来信
Season 1 : Episode 17
Letters from Pegasus

58
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:42,448
那些屏幕上的小点,
它们看起来并不危险, 是不是?
They don't seem threatening,
those dots on the screen, do they?

59
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:45,451
这就是为什么我们要去实地侦察
去获取第一手的资料
Which is why we need to do recon and
see what we're up against firsthand.

60
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:46,911
怎样去?
How ?

61
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:52,041
我已经跟踪了它们的行进路线
幽灵的飞船很显然会周期性的进出超空间
I've been tracking their progress. The Wraith ships
apparently go in and out of hyperspace periodically.

62
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:57,880
- 要么是它们关于超空间的技术十分有限....
- 要么是它们在沿路洗劫
- Either because their hyperspace technology is limited....
- Or they're stopping to feed along the way.

63
00:04:58,256 --> 00:05:00,508
重要的是, 这种行进模式是可以预测的
The point is, the pattern is predictable.

64
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:06,806
我可以断定, 它们会在
这里,  这里和这里停一下
I can guess with some certainty, that
they'll be making stops, here, here and here.

65
00:05:07,431 --> 00:05:11,185
即便是这样, 这些飞船仍然在数光年以外
我们如何让我们的小飞船去接近它们?
Even so, those ships are light years away. How
do you expect to reach them in a puddle jumper?

66
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:16,816
我们可以飞到一个途中的星际之门
Zelenka认为它们会在那里脱离超空间
然后就在旁边观察它们
We fly to a Stargate en route that Zelenka thinks they're
gonna drop out of hyperspace, and we watch them pass by.

67
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:20,111
- 不错
- 你知道我已经准备好了
- That's good.
- You know I have my moments.

68
00:05:20,403 --> 00:05:22,822
我和Teyla刚才已经决定了将去哪个星球
Teyla and I were just deciding which planet to go to.

69
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:25,867
我跟这个星球上的人们很熟
I am familiar with the people of this world.

70
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:30,037
他们的星际之门处于开放状态
可以通过一艘飞船
Their Stargate is in the open,
and so, accessible by ship.

71
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:33,749
你确信在幽灵经过你们的时候
不会被发现?
And you think you can remain undetected
by the Wraith as they go by your position?

72
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,960
隐形模式
它们甚至不知道我们在那里
Stealth mode. They won't even know we're there.

73
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:42,341
好吧, 去吧, 尽可能多的获取信息
记得在Rodney发送消息前回来
我要你们两个都回到这里
OK, go. Get what intel you can and get back before
Rodney sends his message. I need the both of you here.

74
00:05:42,341 --> 00:05:44,051
在任务完成前, 我们是不会停下的
Won't even stop at the duty free.

75
00:06:08,492 --> 00:06:14,373
千万不要试图去和幽灵的飞船交火
我在这里命令你, 不要这样做
On the offchance that you get the idea to take the Wraith
ships on yourself Major. I am hereby ordering you not to.

76
00:06:14,582 --> 00:06:15,791
相信我, 不会的
Believe me you don't have to.

77
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:16,584
再强调一次
<i>Still.</i>

78
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:22,048
"不要只身赤手空拳与敌舰搏斗"
我明白
"Don't take on alien armada's single handedly."
I understand.

79
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:40,816
父亲! Teyla来了!
Father! Teyla's here!

80
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:52,870
Teyla!
Teyla!

81
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:59,293
- Oren! 好久不见了
- 很久了, 瞧你, 变了许多
- Oren! It has been many days.
- Too many. Look at you, you're so different.

82
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:02,004
自从我上次拜访之后
很多东西都发生了改变
Much has changed since my last visit.

83
00:07:04,006 --> 00:07:08,427
- 这位是John Sheppard少校. 这是Oren
- 很高兴见到你
- This is Major John Sheppard. And Oren.
- Pleased to meet you.

84
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:13,558
- 现在离收获还有好几个月
- 是的, 我知道
- The harvest is still months away.
- Yes, I know.

85
00:07:14,475 --> 00:07:17,186
我们到这里来不是为了交易
我们是来提醒你们
We have not come to trade, but to deliver a warning.

86
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:20,731
我们有理由相信幽灵已经在路上
We have reason to believe
the Wraith may be on their way.

87
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:24,068
我们无法确信
不过我们就要去搞清楚
We don't know that for a fact,
but we're about to go and find out.

88
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:27,947
是的, 看起来它们正在到处醒来
Yes, it seems they're awakening everywhere.

89
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:30,992
你应该告诉你的人民
做好防范它们到来的措施
You should tell your people
to take precautions in case they do come.

90
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,159
我会的
I will.

91
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:39,667
不过你也知道, Teyla, 无论你去哪里
它们都有办法找到. 逃不掉的
But you know as well as I do Teyla, that the Wraith will
track us down wherever we go. There will be no escape.

92
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:41,210
那么通过星际之门呢?
What about through the Stargate?

93
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:45,047
洗劫会在很多个星球上发生
没有地方是安全的
The cullings are taking place
on many worlds. None are safe.

94
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:48,050
即便是我们找到了避难所
Even we have taken in refugees.

95
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:56,392
如果他们真的来了, 尽量离星际之门远点
带你的家人到树林的边缘, 那里, 等着我们
If they do come, stay far from the Stargate. Take
your family to the far treeline, there, and wait for us.

96
00:07:56,392 --> 00:07:59,979
- Teyla.
- 一个家庭, 少校, 这就是我的全部要求
- Teyla.
- One family Major, that is all I ask.

97
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:08,070
我很抱歉Oren, 我不能保证
I'm sorry Oren, I can't make that promise.

98
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:10,031
至少, 这是我们可以做到的
It will be the very least we can do.

99
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:16,329
- 如果有时间的话
- 那我们就必须赶紧
- If there's time.
- Then we must hurry.

100
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:27,757
孩子们, 我们必须做好准备
Children, we must prepare.

101
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:33,554
好了, 我们已经准备好了城市的布局图,
任务报告以及作战评估
Alright, we have our city' specs, mission reports
and tactical assessments all ready to go.

102
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:35,515
还有什么?
What else ?

103
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:39,477
我已经附上了一大堆我们所能够解密的
来自古人数据库的数据
Well I've included a ton of data that we've been
able to decipher from the Ancient database.

104
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:42,688
真的么? 难以置信
Really? That is incredible.

105
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:46,270
我所设计的压缩算法非常有效
Well the algorithm I've devised
is extraordinarily efficient, yes.

106
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:47,527
哦, 求你了!
Oh please!

107
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:51,280
必须是这样
否则没办法在1.3秒内发完所有的数据
Well it must be,
in order to fit all that data into 1.3 seconds.

108
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:53,574
事实上, 只用去了0.3 秒
.3 seconds actually.

109
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:55,701
我们还有整整一秒钟来发送数据?
We have a whole extra second to fill?

110
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:58,371
整整一秒钟, 是这样
A whole extra one, yes.

111
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:05,586
足够用来发送个人消息么?
Is it enough to include personal messages?

112
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:11,676
当然, 可以包括几小时的视频
如果我们限制音频的话, 还可以更多
Sure, I mean several hours of video.
Much more if we restrict the audio.

113
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:15,096
我想我们在精神上非常需要这个
特别是现在
I think it'll do wonders for moral. Especially now.

114
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,807
我可以告诉我们的奶奶
我这些时候都做了些什么
I could tell my Grandma
what I've been up to all this time.

115
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:20,852
当然, 如果你的奶奶有足够的安全许可的话
是的, 你可以
Well if your grandmother had security clearance,
yes you could.

116
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:25,147
不过目前, 你可以告诉她
你很好, 而且你很想念她
But for now, you can tell her
that you're well and that you miss her.

117
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:28,818
这些都非常吸引人, 不过,
我还有工作要去做. 我是不是...
This is all very charming, but um,
I have work to do. Shouldn't I...

118
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:32,446
中尉, 也许你可以来处理一下
Lieutenant, maybe you'd like to handle this.

119
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:36,409
给每个人在镜头前几分钟的机会
让他们可以给所爱的人发一条个人消息
Give everybody a few minutes on camera send
a personal message to their loved ones.

120
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,827
我很乐意
I'd love to ma'am.

121
00:09:37,869 --> 00:09:39,120
好了去做吧!
Off you go!

122
00:09:43,082 --> 00:09:46,169
只要我和Zelenka 把四号飞船的引擎
成功接入到能源网
As soon as Zelenka and I can get
Jumper 4's engines tied into the grid,

123
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:48,254
我们就可以进行低能量演练了
we should be able to do a low power dry run.

124
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:49,088
很好
Good.

125
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:50,548
Rodney?
Rodney?

126
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:53,843
你不想给什么人发条消息么?
You don't want to send a message to anyone?

127
00:09:53,885 --> 00:09:58,973
你知道么? 我想我会利用所有的空余时间,
为我自己录制一条消息
You know what? I think with all my spare time,
I'll just record a message to myself.

128
00:09:59,473 --> 00:10:00,558
你认为呢?
You?

129
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:02,185
当然
Yes.

130
00:10:02,852 --> 00:10:04,103
好的, 好的
Good, good.

131
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:15,031
这并不是一个拯救行动
This wasn't supposed to be a rescue mission.

132
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:17,491
Oren是我父亲的好朋友
Oren was a good friend of my father.

133
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:19,744
我想提醒你
I agreed to warn him.

134
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:22,038
如果有人跟你的家人很亲近
If someone close to your family,

135
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:26,459
一个亲近的朋友, 正处于将被幽灵带走的危险之中
你能够无动于衷么?
a dear friend, was in danger of being taken by
the Wraith, would you have not done the same?

136
00:10:26,501 --> 00:10:28,669
如果这危及这次任务, 我会的
Not if it jeopardised the mission.

137
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:33,799
这么说与幽灵斗争, 我们就要舍弃
我们同它们的不同之处么?
So in fighting the Wraith, we are to give up
that which makes us different from them?

138
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:39,222
我同意停下来把他带上, 如果有时间的话
但如果没有时间, 我也无能为力
I agreed to stop and pick him up
if there was time, but only if there was time.

139
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:43,726
如我们可以, 我愿意拯救这个星系中的所有人
I'll be saving everyone
in the damn galaxy, if we could.

140
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:46,270
一个人连同他的孩子不是所有人
One man and his children are not every person.

141
00:10:46,395 --> 00:10:48,731
我同意提供帮助, 如果有时间的话
I agreed to help, if there was time.

142
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:52,902
我们必须量力而行
You only fight the battles you can win.

143
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:35,862
我们转过去看看
Let's get this thing turn around.

144
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:45,246
它们正朝那个星球而去
They're heading for the planet.

145
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:53,588
OK, 开始录了, 电池很足
OK, recording, plenty of battery.

146
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:55,882
为什么我什么也没有看到
So why am I not seeing anything.

147
00:11:56,007 --> 00:11:56,924
真蠢!
Stupid!

148
00:12:10,605 --> 00:12:14,442
OK. 嗨, 爷爷, 奶奶!
OK. Hi Grandma, Grandpa!

149
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:18,196
是我Aiden, 当然
It's me Aiden, obviously.

150
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:22,742
来自一个离家很远, 很远的地方
Talking to you from a place, far, far, from home.

151
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:26,454
我很好, 你们不用担心
I'm good though. You don't have to worry.

152
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:30,416
这里的生活很平常
Life here is pretty routine.

153
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:46,224
我希望不久后就可以回家
不过你们知道, 如果
I'm hoping to get home sometime soon.
But you know, if

154
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:51,437
我不得不在这里多呆一会儿
我希望你们知道我很好
I'm stuck here a while,
I want you to know that I'm good.

155
00:12:52,355 --> 00:12:56,359
我正在做一些我从来没有想到的事情
I'm doing things, seeing things
I never thought I'd see.

156
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:16,838
真希望能告诉你们一切
谁知道呢, 也许某一天, 我就可以跟你们说了
